{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/hearing-loss-in-adults/how-this-topic-was-developed/evidence-exclusion-criteria/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"ab47772d-9c51-52f9-81f5-7756d2284d4a","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field dc6c67ce-39ac-4bc4-9453-aa0600bd1314 --><h2>Evidence exclusion criteria</h2><!-- end field dc6c67ce-39ac-4bc4-9453-aa0600bd1314 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item aab2cc34-8e79-433b-a881-aa0600bd1314 --><!-- begin field 7cf84c67-d24c-4b02-beb5-aa0600bd1314 --><h2>Our policy</h2><!-- end field 7cf84c67-d24c-4b02-beb5-aa0600bd1314 --><!-- begin field dfa9807e-c06a-4785-91df-aa0600bd1314 --><p>Scoping a literature search, and reviewing the evidence for CKS is a methodical and systematic process that is carried out by the lead clinical author for each topic. Relevant evidence is gathered in order that the clinical author can make fully informed decisions and recommendations. It is important to note that some evidence may be excluded for a variety of reasons. These reasons may be applied across all CKS topics or may be specific to a given topic.</p><p>Studies identified during literature searches are reviewed to identify the most appropriate information to author a CKS topic, ensuring any recommendations are based on the best evidence. We use the principles of the GRADE and PICOT approaches to assess the quality of published research. We use the principles of AGREE II to assess the quality of published guidelines.</p><!-- end field dfa9807e-c06a-4785-91df-aa0600bd1314 --><!-- begin field a7bbbd1e-95cb-4ffa-b70d-aa0600bd1314 --><h2>Standard exclusions for scoping literature:</h2><!-- end field a7bbbd1e-95cb-4ffa-b70d-aa0600bd1314 --><!-- begin field cf1112b6-3d9e-44d5-a0bb-aa0600bd1314 --><ul><li>Animal studies</li><li>Original research is not written in English</li></ul><!-- end field cf1112b6-3d9e-44d5-a0bb-aa0600bd1314 --><!-- begin field 324e51c5-75f6-4b49-a273-aa0600bd1314 --><h2>Possible exclusions for reviewed literature:</h2><!-- end field 324e51c5-75f6-4b49-a273-aa0600bd1314 --><!-- begin field cce7c5bd-e964-4a0c-99c0-aa0600bd1314 --><ul><li>Sample size too small or study underpowered</li><li>Bias evident or promotional literature</li><li>Population not relevant</li><li>Intervention/treatment not relevant</li><li>Outcomes not relevant</li><li>Outcomes have no clear evidence of clinical effectiveness</li><li>Setting not relevant</li><li>Not relevant to UK</li><li>Incorrect study type</li><li>Review article</li><li>Duplicate reference</li></ul><!-- end field cce7c5bd-e964-4a0c-99c0-aa0600bd1314 --><!-- end item aab2cc34-8e79-433b-a881-aa0600bd1314 -->","topic":{"id":"04ebfcd5-34b5-50ed-9f39-eb5d18a386dd","topicId":"2f4e8b5b-3e3c-4daf-95b5-aa0600bd0fb1","topicName":"Hearing loss in adults","slug":"hearing-loss-in-adults","lastRevised":"Last revised in September 2019","chapters":[{"id":"6f91987e-3ad1-50d2-9fa8-cb374f1fea65","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"234d842b-e403-5767-84ee-5c7e01fd73df","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"1e784365-09cd-5406-9baa-82e13b39db65","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"976993cf-ed52-538c-895a-e817e69054b2","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"04b1ba81-cc05-5054-96b7-84655edba2ea","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"671eaddd-f19a-5497-80ac-f748bdc43b3d","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"c7d5b46b-876d-50e0-8276-483b363e0125","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"88c30095-2b11-5623-9e81-21310fab6825","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"adf2bb1c-e78f-56bd-8121-102e9f9a0930","slug":"audit-criteria",